namedLocations.description: A ZIP Code is a postal code used by the United States Postal Service (USPS) in a system it introduced in 1963. The term ZIP is an acronym for Zone Improvement Plan; it was chosen to suggest that the mail travels more efficiently and quickly (zipping along) when senders use the code in the postal address. The basic format consists of five digits. An extended ZIP+4 code was introduced in 1983 which includes the five digits of the ZIP Code, followed by a hyphen and four additional digits that reference a more specific location.

transcript.text: Today we will see about the new feature enhanced in version 7.2 User group wise shipping method and flat shipping method.
In all the shipping methods we have provided user group option.
For example, if we go in weight based shipping method action edit, we can see user group option here.
With this feature only those customer who are assigned in the selected user group can see the shipping method.
In this manner we can restrict visibility of the shipping method for the rest of customer who are not added in the selected user groups.
Next we have flat shipping method.

In this new shipping method, when we active the status, go to action and edit here To create a custom shipping method that offers flat shipping as well as free shipping, we have added a new shipping method named Flat Shipping.
By using a combination of flat shipping method and user groups, you can easily offer free shipping to your customers.

This method is useful in situations where you deliver manually to your local customers or they come to your brick and mortar location to pick up their order and therefore don't need to pay for shipping.
Flat shipping can be applied based on state.
Select the states from the drop down and zip codes.
Enter, separated zip code values to offer flat shipping.
Admin can easily duplicate the flat shipping method in and number of times and can create permutation and combination to offer different flat shipping rates according to their need.
Thank you for watching this video.
For any further queries, feel free to reach us on live chat or via e-mail.
